optionItem.description: Streaming.LoadBalancingPolicy defines the algorithm for choosing the connection between the protocol daemon and Transaction Managers that will handle the client generated traffic. The connection is chosen when the client establishes a session and it is used for the lifespan of the user session. Valid values are: Blacklist-Round-Robin, Round-Robin, Blacklist-Random and Random. If the value is set to Round-Robin, first the Transaction Manager is chosen in circular order and then its least used connection is utilized. If the value is set to Random, a random connection from the list of all available connections is utilized. Blacklist-Round-Robin and Blacklist-Random work exactly the same way as Round-Robin and Random, but add a filtering of bad connections. The default and recommended value is Blacklist-Round-Robin.
optionItem.name: Streaming.LoadBalancingPolicy
